                                                                            SQL ( Structured Query Language)

üî¥üü°üü¢SQL stands for Structured Query Language.
It is used to create, manage, and manipulate databases.
SQL is a simple database basic component of database. 
üîµMySQL Environment
          Use MinGW64 (for command-line tools if required)
          Use MySQL Workbench 8.0 CE
          Always set a password for the root user


                                                      Types of Databases 
üõë Relational Databases                                                            üõë Non-Relational Databases (NoSQL)    
Data stored in tables (rows & columns)                                              Data not stored in tables. But stored in  Flexible structure
Uses SQL                                                                            Examples: MongoDB,Cassandra      
Examples:MySQL,PostgreSQL,Oracle                              

MySQL Basic Concepts
Database ‚Üí Folder
Table ‚Üí File
Schema ‚Üí Database structure
Database name ‚Üí Acts like a filename


üî¥üü°üü¢Database Commands
üü†Create Database
CREATE DATABASE database_name;

üü£Use Database
USE database_name;                                       OR         Set it as Default Schema in MySQL Workbench.

üü£Drop (Delete) Database
DROP DATABASE database_name;

üü£Read-Only Mode :: Enable Read-Only Mode
ALTER DATABASE database_name READ ONLY = 1;
Database cannot be dropped while in read-only mode.

üü£Disable Read-Only Mode
ALTER DATABASE database_name READ ONLY = 0;

üü£Creating a Table
CREATE TABLE EMPLOYEE (
    name VARCHAR(50),
    id INT,
    salary DECIMAL(5,3),
    hire_date DATE
);
üü£Data Types Explained
VARCHAR(50) ‚Üí String (max 50 characters)
INT ‚Üí Integer
DECIMAL(5,3) ‚Üí  5 digits total   3 digits after decimal point
DATE ‚Üí Stores date (YYYY-MM-DD)

‚ö†Ô∏è Note:
No comma after the last column
End statement with ;

üü£Select Data
Select All Records from a Table
SELECT * FROM table_name;

üü£Drop Table
DROP TABLE table_name;

üü£Alter Table
Add a Column
ALTER TABLE table_name
ADD phone_number INT;

üü£Modify a Column            
ALTER TABLE table_name                        OR                        ALTER TABLE table_name
MODIFY num INT                                                           MODIFY num INT FIRST;
AFTER name;                             

üü£Drop a Column
ALTER TABLE table_name
DROP COLUMN hire_date;

üü£Rename a Column
ALTER TABLE table_name                 
RENAME COLUMN old_name TO new_name;                                      

Example
ALTER TABLE work
RENAME COLUMN day TO date;
